title.narrative: Capacity and entrepreneurial skills development for sustainable agro-industrialisation

description.narrative: The success of the IAIPs in Ethiopia is to a large extent dependent on adequate readiness of the agriculture commodities value chains to feed the industries that will be established in the parks. In line with this the Government of Ethiopia (GoE) has mobilised funding from the African Development Fund (ADF) and other sources to assist in financing the IAIP project. Specific intervention include: support for enabling infrastructure for IAIP and related RTCs; support in developing capacity and skills for sustainable agro-industrialisation. The GoE further requested UNIDO to provide technical assistance and to be the implementing partner for project component on capacity development and skills development. The integration of small holder farms, small scale processing enterprises and allied industries into commercial value chains as well as developing human capacities and skills along the value chain as well as the capacities of rural populations to benefit from new agribusiness employment opportunities, are some of the interventions needed for the success of the IAIP.
